name: (3S)-3-Acetyl-3-benzyl-5-hydroxy-6,7-dimethoxy-4-methyl-1-benzofuran-2(3H)-one
Reason: 1,2,3,4-Tetrahydroisoquinoline base (melting point around 106°C) with two methoxy groups, a benzyl group, and an acetyl group. The methoxy groups increase the melting point due to the increased molecular weight and van der Waals forces, approximately +10°C each. The benzyl group introduces a rigid structure with potential hydrogen bonding, raising the melting point by approximately +20°C. The acetyl group introduces a carbonyl-like functional group, which can participate in dipole interactions and increase the melting point by approximately +10°C. The tetrahydroisoquinoline base itself has a melting point around 106°C.
